@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}

<div class="container py-5">
    <h1 class="mb-4">@ViewData["Title"]</h1>

    <p class="text-muted">
        Your privacy is important to us. This Smart Lost & Found System is designed
        to help users report and recover lost items while ensuring that personal
        information remains secure and protected.
    </p>

    <h4 class="mt-4">Information We Collect</h4>
    <p class="text-muted">
        We may collect basic user information such as your name, email address,
        and item details when you report a lost or found item. This information is
        used only to facilitate matching and communication between users.
    </p>

    <h4 class="mt-4">How We Use Your Information</h4>
    <p class="text-muted">
        The information you provide is used to:
        <ul>
            <li>Match lost and found items</li>
            <li>Allow users to contact each other securely</li>
            <li>Improve system functionality and user experience</li>
        </ul>
    </p>

    <h4 class="mt-4">Data Protection</h4>
    <p class="text-muted">
        We implement appropriate security measures to protect your personal data.
        Only authenticated users can access item reports, and we do not share your
        information with third parties without your consent.
    </p>

    <h4 class="mt-4">User Responsibility</h4>
    <p class="text-muted">
        Users are responsible for providing accurate information and using the
        platform respectfully. Any misuse of the system may result in restricted access.
    </p>

    <h4 class="mt-4">Changes to This Policy</h4>
    <p class="text-muted">
        This privacy policy may be updated from time to time. Any changes will be
        reflected on this page.
    </p>

    <p class="mt-4 text-muted">
        If you have any questions, please contact the system administrator.
    </p>
</div>